            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[To 
                  <persname>Upton Sinclair</persname>, in French with
                  typed translation.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
      <c01 level="series" id="d1e222">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Letters</unittitle>
        </did>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e226">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>John Dewitt Warmer</persname>to 
                  <persname>Upton Sinclair</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1910 Dec 2</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>TLS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Gives his opinion on the "Warren case," the
                  "Taylor episode," the 
                  <geogname>Colorado</geogname>kidnapping of labor
                  leaders, etc.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e251">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Upton Sinclair</persname>to 
                  <persname>Jack London</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">ca. 1910</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ANS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Includes AN by 
                  <persname>Jack London</persname>, on same page, 1910
                  Dec 12; asks London to sign [a letter]; London
                  agrees.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e276">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Romain Rolland</persname>to 
                  <persname>Upton Sinclair</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1919 Mar 20</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>4 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Acknowledges receipt of Sinclair's book and
                  diary; compliments him; recounts meeting with
                  Professor 
                  <persname>Georg Fr. Nicolai</persname>, a war hero;
                  admires Nicolai because of his great personal
                  courage; says he wrote several articles on the works
                  of Nicolai, including 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Biologie de la Guerre</bibref>and his
                  memoirs; asks him to assist the American translator,
                  Madame 
                  <persname>H. Van Brugh</persname>, in publishing the
                  articles; discusses her talent; says he has shown
                  Nicolai " 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Declarations de l' Independence
                  d'Esprit</bibref>" and approved it; asks him to sign
                  a copy.] (In French with typed translation)</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e310">
          <did>
            <unittitle>[Soviet Ambassador to 
                  <geogname>Switzerland</geogname>] to 
                  <persname>Upton Sinclair</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1919 May 15</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>APCS</genreform>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Requests copies of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Profits of Religion</bibref>and 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Debs' Speech in his Defense</bibref>; says he
                  will send the money for the books through an American
                  socialist woman.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e335">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Ryan Walker</persname>to 
                  <persname>Upton Sinclair</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n.y. Dec 26</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>zAL,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Says he has drawn a diagram of Sinclair at work;
                  mentions concern about J. H.; worries that the
                  reading public will lose interest in his novel after
                  the war; urges him to take "Jimmie" to 
                  <geogname>Russia</geogname>and to bring him back a
                  Bolshevik; includes ink cartoon on side.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
    </dsc>
